      "explanation": "<table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>REM findings on EEG, EOG, EMG</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>EEG (Electroencephalogram)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>\u2022 <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"149fc70e9a16927771864296cb4e21\">EEG</span> activity is increased similar to the awake state (beta activity) along with the return of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a9268f2e1d16927771814cfef69cf4\">alpha</span> activity</p>\n<p>\u2022 The typical appearance of these waves is known as <strong>Sawtooth waves or Sawtooth appearance.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>\u2022 <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5b09a1161b169277719460978e4cc1\">Paradoxical</span> sleep:</strong> Even though the person is sleeping, the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"149fc70e9a16927771864296cb4e21\">EEG</span> shows activity similar to that of the awake state.</p>\n<p><strong>\u2022 PGO (Ponto Geniculo Occipital) spikes</strong> are also seen - Large phasic potentials that originate from <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5e4684038e16927771967a14f73f37\">Pons</span> (the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8656dac49a16927771846b41f8cf19\">cholinergic</span> neurons) and go towards the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fc380e21321692777191739bd99191\">lateral</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"00b4dbe9e4169277718881a95f7864\">geniculate</span> body and to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"77dc7a0ab81692777194dba7ab78ab\">occipital</span> spikes.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>EOG (Electrooculogram)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Rapid eye movements are seen</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>EMG (Electromyogram)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>\u2022 <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"949f14b6e4169277720075eaacbf1f\">Tonic</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3caa3ba2111692777182713201b915\">atonia</span> (as if the muscle is in paralysis) with phasic twitches</p>\n<p>\u2022 It means there is a near-complete loss of muscle tone, preventing movement during vivid dreaming.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"eeg\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"10666\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"April2025\" height=\"337\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/RxlZZSsqYcB8AE8dBMiU1745233882.jpg\" width=\"800\"/></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Stage</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>EEG</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>EOG</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>EMG</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Awake (Stage W)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Alpha waves (8-13 Hz) with eyes closed</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Eye movements and blinks present</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>High <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"949f14b6e4169277720075eaacbf1f\">tonic</span> activity, voluntary movements</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>N1 Stage (Light Sleep) (Option B)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Loss of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a9268f2e1d16927771814cfef69cf4\">alpha</span> waves, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ccb50023dc1692777200804b8475ca\">theta</span> waves (4-7 Hz)</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Slow eye movements</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Tonic activity decreases</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>N2 Stage (Moderate Sleep)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>(Option C)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Sleep spindles (12-14 Hz), K complexes</strong> (sharp negative followed by positive waves)</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>None</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Very low <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"949f14b6e4169277720075eaacbf1f\">tonic</span> activity</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>N3 Stage (Deep Sleep)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>(Option D)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Delta waves (slow, high amplitude)</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>None</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Low <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"949f14b6e4169277720075eaacbf1f\">tonic</span> activity</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
